    <item>
      <title>Unlocking the Mystery of 502 Errors: Root Causes and Solutions</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/502-error-root-causes-and-solutions/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 06:20:21 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/502-error-root-causes-and-solutions/</guid>
      <description>A 502 error is a server error that occurs when a server acting as a gateway or proxy receives an invalid response from an upstream server, often due to overload, misconfiguration, or software bugs. Understanding the root cause is key to resolving the issue.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>502 Bad Gateway Error: Is It You or the Server? Complete 2026 Troubleshooting</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/502-bad-gateway-error-your-fault-or-server/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 18:20:21 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/502-bad-gateway-error-your-fault-or-server/</guid>
      <description>A 502 Bad Gateway error is never the user&amp;rsquo;s fault — it indicates a communication breakdown between servers. The problem lies with the website&amp;rsquo;s hosting, proxy, or upstream server, not your browser or internet connection.</description>
